{
  "_comment": [
    "SHARED cross-language parity table for the decision preview rule (issue #126).",
    "The action->effect rule is duplicated in Python (temporal/src/ops_api/app.py:describe_action_effect)",
    "and TypeScript (frontend-portal/src/portal/lib/agentsApi.ts:describeActionEffect).",
    "Both implementations are pinned to THIS table:",
    "  - temporal/tests/test_decision_preview.py asserts describe_action_effect == cases here.",
    "  - frontend-portal/scripts/verify-decision-preview.mjs EXECUTES the TS describeActionEffect",
    "    and asserts its output == cases here.",
    "If either language's rule changes, this table must change too, which immediately breaks the",
    "other language's test -- so Python and TS can never silently diverge.",
    "Note: value_impact.amount is intentionally null in both (describe_*_effect is PURE over a",
    "FindingRecord that has no price); the monetary figure is the finding's delta, shown in the UI.",
    "The faithful contract is (kind + markdown_pct in params), which is what is pinned here."
